<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Railway Contains:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Route Distance</li>
            <li>Journey Planner</li>
            <li>Shortest Route</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Route Distance</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="">Allow the user to enter a number of stops</a></li>
            <li><a href="">And then print the distance involved in the traversing the route</a></li>
            <li><a href="">If the route can not be traversed because it is invalid</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Then print out an error message</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Test data: A-B-C, A-E-B-C-D, A-D, A-D-C, A-E-D</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Journey Planner</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="">Allow the user to enter a start and end station</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Optionally with a maximum or exact number of "stops" along the way</a></li>
            <li><a href="">The screen should calculate and print out the number of possibilities that exist</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Test data: C to C with a maximum of 3 stops</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h3>Shortest Route</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="">Allow the user to enter a start and end station</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Which could be the same station</a></li>
            <li><a href="">And then print out the length</a></li>
            <li><a href="">And details of the shortest route</a></li>
            <li><a href="">In terms of distance to travel</a></li>
            <li><a href="">Test data: B to B, A to C</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
